node.text: 加油加油加油 ⛽️ 普通人都可能适应不良了，更何况是你。家里有一个精力旺盛的、肚子里还有多一个！💪💪💪

@keweitay maybe @zolalfredo can give Momo tuition class in the evening after dinner and before bed time - reading and writing seems to make the little ones sleepy plus it makes parents happy that the 45 minutes is well spent

Anyone’s bio-clock also completely messed up? 🥵Omg I completely lost it some weeks ago when I felt so overwhelmed by Momo that I turned into a monster and made him face the wall and yelled at him for not sleeping. 🤯
His schedule is now all over the place again, skipping naps, waking late, or sometimes taking naps and ending up sleeping near midnight. So difficult to put him on any kind of schedule as we were still trying to figure out our own. 
He would insist I sleep with him, then make me sleep in an awkward position so he can access my boobs, then toss and turn nonstop till i was so physically uncomfortable and kept drifting to sleep and getting woken by him. 
Eventually I went to my room and just tried to sleep while he climbed all over me like an obstacle course. He eventually crashed into my face and it hurt dammit so I just raged at him. He started crying for Daddy and I said No Daddy!! @zolalfredo was out for a jog so I called him and was such a crying wreck he thought my water broke or some accident happened 😓 
Just wanted to put this out here to remember how #circuitbreakersg can be overwhelming at times, and mums you are not alone ok!! 🥺
📷 @8dayssg 😍
#shenmomo #2y7m #stayhome #sgunited #stayhomeforsg #imstayinghome
Jia You! Eat some happy fruits? @wmeiyan You too! 💪
@shunjimatsuo ❤️
Otsukaresama 🤗 take care! 💕
I know how it feels. I've lost it too many times and I don't know how much more I can take. Not helping that my boy is currently teething and is super hard to feed. Sigh.
Hugs..my toddler does it to me too so I can imagine how uncomfortable it is esp when you are so heavily preg now! Hang in there!
@missamandaleong congrats on being pregnant again babe!!! 😍 You look amazing ❤️

It's happened once last year... 😅 I was sobbing and driving all the way home with the little bugger in the backseat cos he was being such a little devil. Doesn't help that we're feelin' the hormones when we're preggo! But the cutest thing is... They don't remember a thing after that and love you just the same!! 🤣 Cheeky little ones aren't they...
Here I am at 3am with an almost 1yo going through her sleep regression and waking up very often during night! Big hugs!
@serenaong_sg ❤️ testing our patience to the limits!!! Haha
Sending some positivity over. 🙌🏻 I also have such nights where I just rage!!!
Totally, babe! My son's schedule is a mess now and we r struggling to not to be 'monster parents'. Lol..

Thank you for sharing. It helps to know overwhelmed moms are not alone. 😢 I think the cb compounds all the times we see our kid and all the behaviors too omg! No sleep solution here except to exhaust them and then read good nite books to them multiple times!
Oh no.... hope ur still ok
Same situation.
Same situation. Both our toddlers are in the same month. So quite same patterns. Terrible 2 now

@beababbles thanks dear!! I meant he stays awake from 9am to 9pm without naps!! He still can’t sleep through the night, wakes up a few times and usually will even leave his room to come to ours in the middle of the night to sleep in our bed. Haha. Hope you are doing well with your baby too!! ❤️

@keweitay He still wants to seek comfort from papa and mama ! 😅. When em refuses to sleep, I’ll tell her everyone she knows (eg korkor, jiejie, popo, bffs etc) are alr sleeping/resting, so it’s time for em to rest too. It took her a few times to get it, and she settles down eventually. Can try and see if it works on momo ! Mine’s showing terrible two signs which I’ve been trying to convince myself to see it as terrific two instead 😅
@beababbles hehe jiayou!! I went through a parent effectiveness training course and it was really helpful! @better_choice_parenting

Hugs babe. It’s inevitable to have bad days and it’s okay. Reset/restart again tmr and hopefully it’ll get better. What I realise is the first 3 days are the toughest when we wanna change their schedules/habits, but it’ll get easier after that. And actually if momo could sleep through from 9pm-9am, it’s quite good ! He clocks 12 hours of sleep. At their age, it’s about 11-13 hours. You’ve been doing well and doing your best. Don’t be too hard on yourself. You’re the best mum for momo & bb#2, and the best wife for @zolalfredo 😘❤️
@ethelyap so excited for your pregnancy Ethel!! ❤️
Oh no!! Big hugs babe, it’s not an easy time for parents. ❤️❤️❤️

Jia you Daddies & Mommies! You guys are doing great! 💪🏼 We understand that it’s not easy, especially when they refuse to listen or just can’t seem to get through to them that WE’RE BUSY/TIRED! 😢 you are not alone! We’re always here to support and journey with you! 🙆🏻‍♀️ Let’s TRY our best to apply P.E.T. skills such as I-message and Active listening on them ☺️ you can do it! 🙆🏻‍♀️❤️
加油↖(^ω^)↗ 忍❤ .. breathe in, breather out... apply some P.E.T skills from @better_choice_parenting 🤗🤗
tough times happen to everyone, you are not alone. Hang in there. Take deep breathes and pray❤️
Hugshugs! Take care and stay safe! ❤️
Totally feel you! The amazing thing about children is that they forgive and forget quickly when they feel emotinally secure. Hope that other days will be better days for u!
I feel you,  as i have 2y3m baby girl and also pregnant for 21months 😌❤️
